[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Middle Rhine valley banner.jpg"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Burg Rheinstein Trechtingshausen 010-Lh.jpg"],["thumb"],["277px"],["Rheinstein Castle near Trechtingshausen, look from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Assmannshausen"]]}]]},"\n\nThe ",{"type":"'''","value":["Rhine Valley"]}," or ",{"type":"'''","value":["Middle Rhine"]}," (German: ",{"type":"''","value":["Mittelrhein"]},") is the most famous section of the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rhine"]]},", running between the cities of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bonn"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bingen"]]}," (near ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mainz"]]},") in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Germany"]]}," and spanning the states of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["North Rhine-Westphalia"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rhineland-Palatinate"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hesse"]]},".  The section from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Koblenz"]]}," to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bingen"]]},", known as the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Rhine Gorge"]},", is a ",{"type":"[[","value":[["UNESCO World Heritage Site"]]},", and the entire valley is often called \"The Romantic Rhine\".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Cities"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Rhein-Karte.png"],["thumb"],["277px"],["Map of the Rhine River; this article covers the section in yellow"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Bacharach Altkölnischer Hof 682-vh.jpg"],["thumb"],["220px"],[{"type":"[[","value":[["Bacharach"]]},": Altkölnischer Hof"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Oberwesel 707-z.jpg"],["thumb"],["220px"],[{"type":"[[","value":[["Oberwesel"]]},": Haagsturm, behind the Liebfrauenkirche, on the mountain the Schönburg"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bonn"]]},"-Bad Godesberg (west)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Königswinter"]]}," (east)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bad Honnef"]]}," (east)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Unkel"]]}," (east)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Remagen"]]}," (west) — site of the famous World War II bridge"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Linz am Rhein"]]}," (east)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Andernach"]]}," (west)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Neuwied"]]}," (east)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Koblenz"]]}," (west) — where the Mosel river joins the Rhine"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Lahnstein"]]}," (east)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rhens"]]}," (west)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Braubach"]]}," (east)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Boppard"]]}," (west)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["St. Goarshausen"]]}," (east) — right across the river from St. Goar"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["St. Goar"]]}," (west) — opposite the Loreley rock"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Oberwesel"]]}," (west)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kaub"]]}," (east)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bacharach"]]}," (west)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Lorch"]]}," (east)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Assmannshausen"]]}," (east)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bingen"]]}," (west)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rüdesheim"]]}," (east)"]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\nThe Rhine Valley, where the Rhine carves its way through steep hills topped with countless castles and ruins, is one of the most famous and most heavily touristed parts of Germany.  Traveling here is very easy — cruises, castles and winery tours by day, sampling the wine at night — and it's no surprise that the visiting demographic is slanted heavily towards retirees looking for an easy break.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["When to go"]},"\nThe peak season is definitely summer, when the hillsides are green and the cruise boats busy.  In September, many inns and restaurants already start closing down for the winter, and almost all cruises end by November, starting up again in April.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By plane or train"]},"\nThe most common starting points for a tour of the Rhine Valley are ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Cologne"]]},", just north of Bonn, and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Frankfurt"]]},", just east of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rüdesheim"]]},".  Frankfurt is actually on the Main, not the Rhine itself, so the Rhine towns of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mainz"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Wiesbaden"]]}," also make popular starting points.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By cruise"]},"\nA large number of luxury cruise operators sail up (and down) the Rhine from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Amsterdam"]]}," to eg. ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Basel"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Zurich"]]}," or ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Strasbourg"]]},".  The leisurely journey with plenty of stopovers typically takes anywhere from one to two weeks, with accommodation on the boat itself.  Large operators include ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.avalonwaterways.com\/ Avalon"]}]}," and ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.vikingrivers.com\/ Viking"]}]},", with low-season prices for a 7-night cruise starting from around US$2,000.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Marksburg Castle Rhine River Valley Braubach Germany.JPG"],["thumb"],["170px"],["Marksburg, the only unaltered castle along the Rhine Valley"]]},"\nThe ",{"type":"'''","value":["Rheinland-Pfalz-Ticket"]}," ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.vrminfo.de\/en\/tickets-and-fares\/ticket-offers\/rheinland-pfalz-ticket\/ "]}," lets groups of ",{"type":"''","value":["up to five people"]}," travel freely for a day (9 AM onwards on weekdays, all days weekends, up to 3 AM of the following day) by train, bus and local transport within the state of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rhineland-Palatinate"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Wiesbaden"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bonn"]]}," Hbf (only train) for €23 for a single person, €27 for two person and €39 for five person ",{"type":"<","value":["small",["(2013)"]]},".  In addition to the core stretch along the Rhine (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Remagen"]]},"-",{"type":"[[","value":[["Oberwesel"]]}," inclusive) and the train line along the Mosel, the ticket also covers a few handy train stretches outside state boundaries, notably Rolandseck-",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bonn"]]},", Koblenz-",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rüdesheim"]]},"-",{"type":"[[","value":[["Wiesbaden"]]}," and Wiesbaden-",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mainz"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By train"]},"\nThere are not one but two train lines running along this section of the Rhine.  The scenic ",{"type":"'''","value":["Linke Rheinstrecke"]}," (\"Left Rhine Line\") runs along the left (west) bank of the river from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Cologne"]]}," to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mainz"]]},", while the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Rechte Rheinstrecke"]}," (\"Right Rhine Line\") runs along the right (east) bank of the river from Cologne to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Wiesbaden"]]},".  The ",{"type":"''","value":["Linke"]}," side, generally considered the more scenic of the two, is more heavily trafficked and has InterCity services, while the ",{"type":"''","value":["Rechte"]}," side is mostly dedicated to cargo and is limited to regional passenger trains running less than once per hour.  Interchanging between the two is possible at ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Koblenz"]]},"; the city is on the left, but some trains running on the ",{"type":"''","value":["Rechte"]}," start or terminate in there.\n\nBeware that, if you're buying individual tickets, train zones get confusing and pricy fast.  While the \"core\" of the Rhine Valley is in Rhineland-Pfalz's VRM and RNN tariff zone, the Rheingau stretch east of Lorch is also in Frankfurt's RMV zone, while going north of Remagen passes into Cologne's VRS area.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By boat"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Bacharach Ferry.JPG"],["thumb"],["Ferry passing ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bacharach"]]}]]},"\n\nThe ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.k-d.de\/english\/home\/ Köln-Düsseldorfer Rheinschiffahrt"]}]},", better known as ",{"type":"'''","value":["KD"]},", runs cruises and scheduled services up and down the river between ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Cologne"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mainz"]]},".  The summer season (May-Sept) sees up to 8 services daily on the busiest parts of the river, but services are cut considerably in the shoulder seasons of April and October and slow down to a trickle in the winter.  Traveling end to end takes over 11 hours (€49 one way), so most travellers opt for much smaller segments: ",{"type":"[[","value":[["St. Goar"]]}," to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bingen"]]},", for example, passes by the famous rock of Loreley, takes about 90 minutes and costs €15.30.\n\nWhile KD has the most extensive network and schedules, there is quite a bit of competition. For example, ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.bingen-ruedesheimer.com\/rhine-cruise\/index.html Bingen-Rüdesheimer"]}]}," operates scheduled services on the south half between Rüdesheim and St. Goar.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["On foot"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" The ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Rheinsteig"]]}]}," walking trail passes on the right Rhine side through (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Wiesbaden"]]},"), ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rüdesheim"]]},", Lorch, Kaub, Braubach, Lahnstein, Koblenz-Ehrenbreitstein, Neuwied, Linz am Rhein, ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bad Honnef"]]}," and (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bonn"]]},"). "]},{"type":"*","value":[" The ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Rheinburgenweg"]]}]}," walking trail passes on the left Rhine side through ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bingen"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bacharach"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["St. Goar"]]},", Boppard, ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Koblenz"]]},", Andernach, Ramagen and Rolandseck near ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bonn"]]},"-Mehlen."]},{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Rhine River Gorge from Loreley Rock Germany.JPG"],["thumb"],["190px"],["An early spring Rhine River Gorge, viewed from atop Loreley Rock"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":[" See "]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Bacharach Burg Stahleck 635-z f+k.jpg"],["thumb"],["180px"],["Bacharach: Burg Stahleck"]]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Loreley"]},", opposite ",{"type":"[[","value":[["St. Goar"]]}]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":[" Castles "]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" Brömserburg Castle · ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rüdesheim"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" Boosenburg Castle · ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rüdesheim"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" Klopp Castle ",{"type":"''","value":["(Burg Klopp)"]}," · ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bingen"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" Mäuseturm (Toll Tower) · ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bingen"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" Ehrenfels Castle Ruin ",{"type":"''","value":["(Burgruine Ehrenfels)"]}," · ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rüdesheim"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" Rheinstein Castle · ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Trechtingshausen"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" Reichenstein Castle · ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Trechtingshausen"]]}," "]},{"type":"*","value":[" Sooneck Castle · ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Niederheimbach"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" Heimburg Castle · ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Niederheimbach"]]}," "]},{"type":"*","value":[" Fürstenberg Castle Ruins · ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rheindiebach"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" Stahleck Castle · ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bacharach"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" Stahlberg Castle Ruins · Bacha