{"type":"[[","value":[["Koblenz"]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Rhein in Flammen"]}," ",{"type":"''","value":["(Rhine in Flames)"]},": "]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"*","value":[" Linz am Rhein - ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bonn"]]},": 3. May 2014"]}]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rüdesheim"]]}," - ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bingen"]]},": 5. July 2014 and 4. July 2015"]}]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"*","value":[" Spay - ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Koblenz"]]},": 9. August 2014 "]}]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"*","value":["  Oberwesel: 14. Sept. 2013 – The “Night of a Thousand Fires” has been traditionally staged at Oberwesel. For this spectacle, 50 illuminated ships convoy to the town of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["St. Goar"]]}," to watch the illumination of the legendary Loreley rock rising 300 feet out of the river. The procession will go from there upstream to Oberwesel passing towns, castles, and churches bathed in Bengal lights.  The musical brilliant firework display in front of the medieval backdrop of Oberwesel is the highlight of the boat parade."]}]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"*","value":["  St. Goar - St. Goarshausen:  21. Sep. 2013"]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["do"],["name=",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rheinsteig"]]}],["alt="],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Walk part of the trail on the right Rhine side."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["do"],["name=",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rheinburgenweg"]]}],["alt="],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Walk part of the trail on the left Rhine side."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\nThe Rhine Valley is famous for wine, and this section of the Rhine along with its tributaries the Mosel and Nahe cover 5 of Germany's 13 officially recognized wine regions.  From north to south:\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"''","value":["Mosel"]},": mostly sweet white Riesling, covers the entire Mosel River valley from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Luxembourg"]]}," to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Koblenz"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"''","value":["Mittelrhein"]},": almost all Riesling, from Koblenz to Bingen (left bank) and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Königswinter"]]}," to Kaub (right bank)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"''","value":["Nahe"]},": varies wines, along the Nahe river southwest of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bingen"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"''","value":["Rheingau"]},": the best-known, almost all high-quality (",{"type":"''","value":["Prädikat"]},") Riesling, but Assmannshausen's red ",{"type":"''","value":["Spätburgunder"]}," (Pinot Noir) is also famous; right bank only, from Lorch via Assmannshausen, ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rudesheim"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Eltville"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Wiesbaden"]]}," to Hochheim am Main"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"''","value":["Rheinhessen"]},": Germany's largest producer, along the left bank from Bingen through Mainz and south all the way to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Worms"]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Stay safe"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Connect"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.welterbe-mittelrheintal.de\/index.php?id=318&L=3 Upper Middle Rhine World Heritage Site"]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Go next"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bonn"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bad Neuenahr-Ahrweiler"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Burg Eltz"]},", near ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Treis-Karden"]]}," on the Mosel"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bad Kreuznach"]]}," (Nahe)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Ingelheim"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mainz"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rheingau"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Wiesbaden"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mosel Valley"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Eifel"]]}]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["geo"],["50.364167"],["7.605556"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["IsPartOf"],["Germany"]]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["usableregion"]]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["Related"],["UNESCO_World_Heritage_List"]]},"\n\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Wikipedia:Middle Rhine"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Commons:Category:Mittelrhein"]]}]